<p>I have an XML document with this schema:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"&gt;   &lt;xs:element name="numbers"&gt;     &lt;xs:complexType&gt;       &lt;xs:all&gt;         &lt;xs:element name="number1" type="xs:integer"/&gt;         &lt;xs:element name="number2" type="xs:integer"/&gt;         &lt;xs:element name="number3" type="xs:integer"/&gt;         &lt;xs:element name="number4" type="xs:integer"/&gt;         &lt;xs:element name="number5" type="xs:integer"/&gt;       &lt;/xs:all&gt;     &lt;/xs:complexType&gt;   &lt;/xs:element&gt; &lt;/xs:schema&gt; </code></pre>  <p>For example, </p>  <pre><code>&lt;numbers&gt;    &lt;number1&gt;10&lt;/number1&gt;    &lt;number2&gt;20&lt;/number2&gt;    &lt;number3&gt;30&lt;/number3&gt;    &lt;number4&gt;40&lt;/number4&gt;    &lt;number5&gt;50&lt;/number5&gt; &lt;/numbers&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I would like to amend this schema so that each of the numbers must be greater than the last. That is, number2 > number1, number3 > number2, number4 > number3, and number5 > number4. I don't think it's possible with plain XSD, but is it possible with XPATH inside of XSD?</p>